Place @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small bowl{}; bring to room temperature. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @shallot{1}(halved and sliced); finely dice remaining half. Halve @ciabatta bread{1}; trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%oz}; halved @red grapes{2.25%oz}.

In a second #small microwave-safe bowl{} combine sliced shallot, @red wine vinegar{1%tbsp}, @water{1%tsp}, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, and a @salt{pinch}. Microwave for ~{30%seconds}. Set aside to pickle, tossing occasionally.

> Use 2 TBSP vinegar, 2 tsp water, and ½ tsp sugar for 4 servings.

Slice @bacon{4%oz} crosswise into ½-inch pieces.

Heat a #large dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Add bacon in an even layer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until fat is rendered and bacon is crispy, ~{5-8%minutes}.

> Lower heat if bacon begins to brown too quickly.

Transfer bacon to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Discard all but a thin layer of bacon fat (you'll use it to cook the chicken).

While bacon cooks, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Return pan with bacon fat to medium-high heat (add a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} if needed). Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> If chicken is on the thicker side, reduce heat to medium after flipping and cover with a
lid until cooked through, 5-7 minutes.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #cutting board{} and tent with #foil{} to keep warm. Wipe out any burned bits from pan.

Toast ciabatta.

Add half the @garlic powder{1%tsp} to bowl with softened butter; stir to combine. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Spread cut sides of bread with garlic butter and halve on a diagonal.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms, diced shallot, @dried thyme{1%tsp}, a small pinch of salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring, until golden and softened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Stir in @flour{1%tbsp} and remaining garlic powder; cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Add remaining vinegar and cook until liquid is absorbed, ~{1%minute} more.

Reduce heat to medium; add @chicken demi-glace{1} and half the bacon, and @water{1/2%cup}. Cook, stirring, until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted.

> Add a splash of water if sauce is too thick.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @mixed greens{2%oz}, grapes, and pickled shallot with its liquid. Add @olive oil{2%tbsp} and toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken, salad, and garlic bread between plates. Spoon sauce over chicken and top salad with remaining bacon. Serve.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145º.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.